  "text": "So we may naturally extend φ a = (ρ a /ρ) n−2γ 2 onto X. It is known that the map a → φ a and g a is C 0 . By the expansion of metric (4.2) near a, one knows φ a (a) = 1. Therefore |ρ a /ρ − 1| ≤ Cδ near a. By the works of Palatucci and Pisante [CITATION_1] and Fang and González [CITATION_2] , it is not hard to see the following profile decomposition",
